{
  "text": "In situ stress measurements were done using a multiple-beam optical stress sensor (MOSS) during deposition of \ue103lms (see the schematic in Fig. 1 and ESI S-1 \u2020 for more), details of which are mentioned in our previous publication. [CITATION_1] These YSZ \ue103lms are cubic (8 mol% or 15 wt%). All the (111) and (100) YSZ \ue103lms are of $70 and $400 nm respectively. It is observed that in order to obtain (100) YSZ \ue103lms, it is necessary to grow \ue103lms thicker than 250 nm. Annealing of these YSZ \ue103lms was carried out at 1000 C for one hour in ambient conditions. q-2q scans and uscans of these as-deposited and annealed YSZ \ue103lms were done by using a Rigaku Smart lab X-ray diffractometer using Cu-Ka radiation. AFM images of the \ue103lms were taken using Bruker Dimension ICON with ScanAsyst2.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "96786139",
    "135870242",
